```
Create a function extractUserData(user, fields) that takes a user object and an array of fields and uses destructuring to extract specific fields from a user object. The function should handle nested objects. The function should return a new object with the properties specified in the fields array.

// Sample Test Code
const user = {
  id: 1,
  profile: {
    name: "John Doe",
    email: "john@example.com",
    preferences: {
      theme: "dark",
      notifications: true
    }
  },
};

// Test cases
console.log(extractUserData(user, ['id', 'profile.name', 'profile.preferences.theme']));
// Expected: { id: 1, name: "John Doe", theme: "dark" }

console.log(extractUserData(user, ['profile.email', 'profile.preferences.notifications']));
// → { email: 'john@example.com', notifications: true }
```